Remarks
. 

Tyrphonothrus gringai


sp. nov.

differs from other members of the genus by the following combination of characters: 
1
) the densely porose notogaster; 
2
) with setae 
e
2
, 
h
1-2
and 
p
1-3
much longer than others; 
3
) the centrodorsal and laterodorsal ridges linked with M-shaped posterior ridges; 
4
) the pear-shaped notogaster; 
5
) the barbed idiosomal setae (the anal setae, those on epimeres I and II and 

3
a

are smooth); 
6
) with five pairs of genital setae sub-equal in length.
